parameters:
Thug: If I remember correctly, the Jagged Mart was a
convenience store that went under after the original owner
skipped town in the night. Shark Broccoli took it over and
DIY'd it into a grand reopening after he formed the dark
organization. In the beginning, with no know-how, they
really struggled, I heard.

Memimi: That's an old tale only known by the veteran
monsters of the organization... It was back when I was still
in the orphanage. Now, I've taken over much of the
management, but when I think about how they started from
scratch, I can't help but respect them.

Thug: Personally, I think it's pretty clever to offer free
blowjobs inside the convenience store and then start selling
sex rights. It must be incredibly tough to do such
physically demanding work...

Memimi: Never mind about me... Please don't bring it up
again... Working is really hard... ugh...

Thug: I'd totally forgotten, but come to think of it, there
used to be a pro wrestling organization in the city. They
only had three wrestlers and went under before they could
even have a match. The Monster Fight venue is actually on
the site of that old ring.

Memimi: That wrestling organization was once led by the
great Shark Broccoli-sama... So that venue was provided by
him. He really was deeply involved in the launch of Monster
Fight...

Thug: Back then, Shark Broccoli... I mean, the wrestler
Sharkyama was head over heels for a designer girl. If I
remember correctly, she dumped Sharkyama and got together
with his junior, Orcazawa. Just remembered that...

Memimi: Orcazawa, that means Orca Mayor, right... There was
a woman with bad taste... going after someone a bit
stronger, wilder, and with more money...

Memimi: ...Well, can't be helped, I guess... The great
leader was kind of... just the type to end up being... just
a nice person...

Thug: I can't believe you even took down Cerberus Octopus...
We're seriously considering coming under your organization's
umbrella. Our small-time group has been dwindling and
getting poorer by the day...

Memimi: We welcome you anytime... Our organization is quite
white-collar and homey, so I recommend it! I have a few
ideas for new rackets that we could start once we have more
people...

Thug: Even after we took pussy photos non-stop, spread them
everywhere, and made a laughing stock out of you, you're
still this forgiving... You're one hell of a monster... I
underestimated you...

Memimi: ...I don't dwell on the past... I don't engage in
petty bullying, so rest assured... Besides, there are too
many people who took photos and uploaded them to the net, I
don't have time to punish them all... ufufu...

Thug: If we win, Shark Broccoli becomes mayor, if we lose,
she debuts in an adult video... I mean... this is seriously
a high-stakes gamble...

Memimi: Without a doubt, this will be the greatest showdown
ever... It's not just about me, it's a monster fight that
involves the future of the entire city. This time, no one is
an outsider... especially those from the dark
organization...

Thug: I really want us to win, but I also want to see her AV
debut... Isn't there some kind of compromise that could make
both happen...
Memimi: As if that would be acceptable...

Mysterious Being: All the monsters in Dorotoku City wear
monster suits when they transform. It's to hide their faces
and identities... It seems that Shark Broccoli was the first
one in the city to adopt this style.

Mysterious Being: Shark Broccoli was seriously strong...
Truly a monster worthy of the name, with overwhelming power
and toughness... Deep down, everyone probably admired him
and wanted to imitate him...

Memimi: The great boss is truly amazing...! I, as a
subordinate, will inherit the culture of monsters that
started with him, unify the entire organization, and add a
new page to the legend...

Mysterious Being: The things you've done are already
legendary enough... A monster who assaults a celebrity on
live TV is something that won't come around again...

Memimi: Maybe that kind of legend wasn't needed... I've
created a mountain of terrible black history...

Monster: If only our organization had monsters capable of
fighting in Monster Fights, we could have grown bigger...
The top monsters in the city are as strong as professional
fighters... There's no way we can win...

Memimi: Indeed, those who learned martial arts as humans
tend to become strong monsters. Like me and the great
boss... that detestable Orca Mayor was into wrestling...
Anomalocaris was into karate, and Cerberus Octopus was into
boxing...

Monster: Shark Broccoli used to be a professional wrestler,
right? He trained his promising subordinates rigorously...
Lately, only Shark Duke has been fighting, but it's quite a
martial organization...

Memimi: Originally, our organization had the four strongest
kings, including myself. But during the battle royale to
decide who would participate in the Monster Fight, I ended
up injuring everyone, and their monster suits are still
being repaired...
